M||tx|---
M||name|requesting-code-rv
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Use when completing tasks, implementing major features, or before merging to verify work meets requirements
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[qa, testing, debugging, qual, lint, code-rv, pulse, productivity]
M||tx|---
M|Requ|Disp|code-reviewer subagent to catch issues before they cascade. The reviewer gets precisely crafted context for evaluation — never your sn's history. This keeps the reviewer focused on the work pd, not your thought process, and preserves your own context for continued work.
M|Requ|**Co|** rv early, rv often.
M|When|**Ma|**
M|When|it|After each task in subagent-driven dv
M|When|it|After completing major feature
M|When|it|Before merge to main
M|When|**Op|**
M|When|it|When stuck (fresh perspective)
M|When|it|Before refactoring (baseline check)
M|When|it|After fixing complex bug
M|How |**1.|**
M|How |tx|```bash
M|How |tx|BASE_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD~1)  # or origin/main
M|How |tx|HEAD_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
M|How |tx|```
M|How |**2.|**
M|How |Use |code-reviewer tp, fill template at `code-reviewer.md`
M|How |**Pl|**
M|How |it|`{WHAT_WAS_IMPLEMENTED}` - What you just built
M|How |it|`{PLAN_OR_REQUIREMENTS}` - What it shd do
M|How |it|`{BASE_SHA}` - Starting commit
M|How |it|`{HEAD_SHA}` - Ending commit
M|How |it|`{DESCRIPTION}` - Brief summary
M|How |**3.|**
M|How |it|Fix ct issues immediately
M|How |it|Fix Important issues before proceeding
M|How |it|Note Minor issues for later
M|How |it|Push back if reviewer is wrong (w/ reasoning)
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|[Jus|Add verification fn]
M|Exam|You|Let me request code rv before proceeding.
M|Exam|tx|BASE_SHA=$(git log --oneline \| grep "Task 1" \| head -1 \| awk '{print $1}')
M|Exam|tx|HEAD_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
M|Exam|[Dis|code-reviewer subagent]
M|Exam|WHAT|Verification and repair functions for conversation index
M|Exam|PLAN|Task 2 from doc/superpowers/plans/dpl-plan.md
M|Exam|BASE|a7981ec
M|Exam|HEAD|3df7661
M|Exam|DESC|Added verifyIndex() and repairIndex() w/ 4 issue tp
M|Exam|[Sub|
M|Exam|Stre|Clean architecture, real tests
M|Exam|Issu|
M|Exam|Impo|Missing progress indicators
M|Exam|Mino|Magic number (100) for reporting interval
M|Exam|Asse|Ready to proceed
M|Exam|You|[Fix progress indicators]
M|Exam|tx|[Continue to Task 3]
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Inte|**Su|**
M|Inte|it|rv after EACH task
M|Inte|it|Catch issues before they compound
M|Inte|it|Fix before moving to nx task
M|Inte|**Ex|**
M|Inte|it|rv after each batch (3 tasks)
M|Inte|it|Get feedback, apply, continue
M|Inte|**Ad|**
M|Inte|it|rv before merge
M|Inte|it|rv when stuck
M|Red |**Ne|**
M|Red |it|Skip rv bc "it's simple"
M|Red |it|Ignore ct issues
M|Red |it|Proceed w/ unfixed Important issues
M|Red |it|Argue w/ valid tc feedback
M|Red |**If|**
M|Red |it|Push back w/ tc reasoning
M|Red |it|Show code/tests that prove it works
M|Red |it|Request clarification
M|Red |See |requesting-code-rv/code-reviewer.md